The force is looking into four reports of historical offences from 1982, 1985, 2010 and 2016, it said. The statement did not name Mr Westwood, 64. The news came as a BBC internal review concluded the corporation should have further explored issues raised about the DJ during his 20 years at the broadcaster. It has now appointed an independent barrister to lead a broader review. Westwood "strongly" denies any wrongdoing.